  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_1' aria-label=\" The Cosmos Co. Operative Bank Ltd. versus Central Bank of India & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('1','2025','2025_2_1091_1141','2025INSC243'); ><font size='4'> <strong>THE COSMOS CO. OPERATIVE BANK LTD.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>CENTRAL BANK OF INDIA & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 2 S.C.R. 1091</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 243</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010003012025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : J.B. PARDIWALA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, R MAHADEVAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether &lsquo;equitable mortgages&rsquo; are recognized in India under the nomenclature of &lsquo;charge&rsquo; in terms of Section 100 of the Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (TPA); Who holds a valid mortgage over the property&mdash;the Appellant (Cosmos Co. Operative Bank Bank of India). Headnotes&dagger; Transfer of Property Act, 1882 &ndash; Sections 58, 100 &ndash; Equitable mortgage &ndash; Equitable mortgages are recognized in India as a &lsquo;charge&rsquo; under Section 100 of the TPA &ndash; Charge created by equitable mortgage will be enforceable<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 04-02-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 1565/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_2_1091_1141','2025INSC243','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>